reviews.review_text: Deal? Deal! I didn't attend this show. I didn't have to, because due to some strange atmospheric phenomenon, I could hear the music quite plainly from our backyard in a suburb 6 miles away. I was only 15, but that experience lit a fire under me that still hurts like hell in a good way. It's just as well that I didn't go considering the brouhaha that finished the evening. In that bicentennial year, there was an amazing series of shows at Colt-- Stills-Young/Poco, Starship/Fleetwood Mac, Geils/Tull, James Taylor, Kiss, Frampton, Yes; an all-star summer. I'm giving 4 stars bc there's a lot of crowd noise. Samson and Delilah is awesome, you can tell that them guys are having a LOT of fun.
